The '''bile up''' (or boil-up) is considered the cultural dish of the [[Belizean Kriol people|Kriol]]s of [[Belize]].  It is a combination of [[boiled eggs]], [[fish]] and/or [[Domestic pig|pig tail]], with [[cassava]], [[Yam (vegetable)|yam]]s, or [[sweet potato]]es, [[Plantain (cooking)|plantains]], and [[tomato sauce]].

