'''Garanimals''' is an American line of children's related clothing separates, created by Seymour Lichtenstein in 1972 for '''Garan Incorporated'''. Each item of clothing features a hang-tag depicting one of several animal characters called Garanimals.

In February 2008 the brand was relaunched in the US, and is sold exclusively by [[Walmart]], in its stores and online.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/creativity/it-took-three-child-actors-get-scene-right-new-garanimals-ad-173891/|title=It Took Three Child Actors to Get This Scene Right in the New Garanimals Ad|work=[[AdWeek]]|accessdate=10 June 2018}}</ref> Garan is currently owned by [[Berkshire Hathaway]], which also owns [[Fruit of the Loom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/286189/garanimals-you-wore-them-once-now-its-your-kids.html|title=Garanimals: You Wore Them Once, Now It's Your Kids' Turn|work=[[MediaPost Communications]]|accessdate=10 June 2018}}</ref>

