{{for|the Byzantine unit|Pound (mass)#Byzantine litra{{!}}Byzantine litra}}
[[File:Himera AR Litra ca 430 86000020.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A litra from Sicily, ca.&nbsp;430&nbsp;BC.]] 
A '''litra''' (plural: '''litrae'''; {{lang-grc|λίτρα}}) is a small [[silver coin]] (or [[Units of measurement|unit of measurement]] for other [[precious metals]]) used in the [[Colonies_of_Ancient_Greece#Greek_colonies|colonies of Ancient Greece]] in general and in ancient [[Sicily]] in particular. As a coin, the litra was similar in value to the [[Obolus|obol]]<ref>{{cite book |title=A Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities |editor=William Smith |edition=3rd American |location=New York |publisher=Harper & Brothers |year=1845 |page=594 |url=http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0063%3Aalphabetic+letter%3DL%3Aentry+group%3D2%3Aentry%3Dlitra-cn |accessdate=25 July 2011}}</ref> and weighed one-third of a [[Ancient Roman units of measurement|Roman libra]], i.e. {{convert|109.15|g|abbr=on}}.<ref name="BNP">{{cite web |url=http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/brill-s-new-pauly/litra-e707740 |first=Gerd |last=Stumpf |title=Litra |work=[[Brill's New Pauly]] |accessdate=25 July 2011}}{{subscription required}}</ref> In silver, the coin weighed {{convert|0.87|g|abbr=on}} and was equal to one-fifth of a [[drachma]].<ref name="BNP" />

In the 3rd-century [[New Testament apocrypha|apocryphal New Testament]] text known as the ''[[Acts of Thomas]]'', [[Jesus]] sells Thomas to an [[Indian people|Indian]] merchant "for three litrae of silver unstamped".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gnosis.org/library/actthom.htm |title=The Acts of Thomas |work=Gnostic Scriptures and Fragments |publisher=Gnostic Society Library |accessdate=25 July 2011}}</ref>

In the [[Talmud]], the litra is a [[Biblical and Talmudic units of measurement|unit of measurement]], the equivalent of 60 [[shekels]], weighing {{convert|354|g|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/news/torah-archaeology-sheds-light-on-ancient-talmudic-dispute-1.383343 |title='Torah archaeology' sheds light on ancient Talmudic dispute |first=Yair |last=Ettinger |publisher=Haaretz |date=9 September 2011 |accessdate=9 September 2011}}</ref>
