The '''Meister Eckhart Prize''' is a biannual award consisting of a prize of €50,000 given to "thinkers who produce high-quality work on the subject of [[identity (social science)|identity]]" by the ''Identity Foundation''. The prize is named after [[Meister Eckhart]] (1260–1328), a German [[theology|theologian]], [[philosopher]] and [[mysticism|mystic]].
