[[File:LaTentaciónDeLloImposible.jpg|thumb|First edition (Spanish)]]
'''''The Temptation of the Impossible''''' ({{Lang-es|La tentación de lo imposible}}, 2004) is a book-length [[essay]] by Peruvian novelist [[Mario Vargas Llosa]] which examines [[Victor Hugo]]'s ''[[Les Misérables]]''. 

An English translation was published in 2007 and is reviewed in [[Graham Robb]], "In His Nightmare City" ''[[The New York Review of Books]]'' 54/11 (28 June 2007) : 52-54. 

